Remove a Specific Character | Remove all occurrences of a specific character from a string. 

import java.util.*;
class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        String str = "Banana";
        char ch = 'a';
        StringBuilder s = new StringBuilder();
        for(int i=0;i<str.length();i++){
            char c = str.charAt(i);
            if(c==ch){
                continue;                    // skip
            }else{
                s.append(c);
            }
        }
        System.out.println(s.toString());
    }
}

output:
Bnn
